### ‚úÖ Option 1: Modify the Page (Recommended for Full Control)

You **add a small JavaScript snippet** directly to the page‚Äôs `<head>` or `<body>` to detect the `copy` event and push it to the data layer:

```js
document.addEventListener('copy', function(event) {
    const copiedText = document.getSelection().toString();
    if (copiedText.trim() !== '') {
        window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
        window.dataLayer.push({
            event: 'text_copied',
            copied_text: copiedText
        });
    }
});
```

This gives you **reliable and flexible** tracking with full access to the copied text.

üîß **Yes, this requires a small code edit on the page**.

